explanations.text: Balance assesses the ability to remain steady and minimize motion while balancing on a single limb, and is an important component of movement health.
explanations.title: What is Balance?

explanations.text: Asymmetry measures the difference in balance capabilities between right and left limbs, with typical values ranging between 0% and 20%. Small variations in Asymmetry are common due to natural variability and are typically not significant.
explanations.title: What is Asymmetry?

issues.text: Lower Balance scores reflect poorer balance capabilities, which may indicate an increased risk.
Balance capabilities can be affected by fatigue, vestibular system issues, neurological disorders, or musculoskeletal issues such as muscle weakness, limited flexibility, or joint pain and injury.
High magnitudes of Asymmetry may be related to pre-existing or previous injury, reveal existing compensation or specialization, and can be present during injury rehabilitation.
